I was looking for videos to help my sex therapy clients expand their repertoires. I have several of the Sinclair Inst. videos but find them somewhat off-putting. The couples are TOO physically perfect. Not that the ones in these videos are less than physically fit, but they are "ordinary" enough for my clients to be able to identify. In addition Bernie Zilbergeld and Lonnie Barbach are very well-known experts and pioneers, with many years of experience. (Bernie Zilbergeld died in 2002, which does put an obvious date on these videos, but does not detract from them.) Their commentaries are very helpful.

These Alexander Institute videos while they are very "entertaining" are a good antidote for my recent client whose only exposure to other people's sexual behavior was on-line porno. Not a very good one. In these videos, the couples are "making love" not just using each others bodies to get off.
